<body lang=3DEN-US link=3D"#467886" vlink=3D"#96607D" style=3D'tab-interval=
:.5in;
word-wrap:break-word'>

<div class=3DWordSection1>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Ive been working with my team on creating temporary m=
ounting
solutions for Cisco Cameras. We often must set up a space to demonstrate Ci=
sco
Video Endpoints in a customer conference room where we cant mount cameras =
to
the walls. I was working with my team and someone suggested using Speaker
stands which are inexpensive and light but also sturdy. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>I worked through several revisions with this current r=
evision
using all the built-in mounting hardware so you dont have to remove anythi=
ng
from the cameras, and you can use the quick connects to quickly and easily =
mount
and remove the cameras from the mounts for assembly and disassembly.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Ive used FilaCube PLA 2 in black as Ive found it pri=
nts well
but any filament would do. PETG would work well and the PTZ4K mount with its
large flat surface could easily use a glass or carbon infused filament as t=
hose
tend to warp less for large flat pieces.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>These are designed to fit a standard speaker stand. Th=
e ones
I choose are: <a
href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00TUBQ4NM?ref_=3Dppx_hzsearch_conn_dt_b_=
fed_asin_title_1">Gemini
Sound ST-Pack Heavy Duty Professional Audio Universal DJ Fold-Out Telescopi=
ng
Tripod Steel Speaker Stands (Set of 2)<o:p></o:p></a></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>I chose these because they are a little taller than so=
me
others I looked at and they come in pairs in a handy travel bag.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'> </span>However, I believe that most speakers <=
span
class=3DGramE>stands</span> use a 35mm pole which is what these mounts are
designed to use.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>The extrusions for the Quad Camera and Bar Pro mount a=
re
standard 2040 aluminum extrusions. I used 500mm length but you could get aw=
ay
with 400mm for the Quad <span class=3DGramE>camera</span> but the Bar Pro n=
eeds
the 500mm. I chose these: <a
href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08X4NH88C?ref_=3Dppx_hzsearch_conn_dt_b_=
fed_asin_title_4&amp;th=3D1">IXGNIJ
2pcs 500mm V Slot 2040 Aluminum Extrusion</a> but any would do. You also ne=
ed T
Nuts and M5x8mm screws. A kit like <a
href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0F1BWQ35S?ref=3Dppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_=
title&amp;th=3D1">200pcs
2020 Series M5 T Nut and Black Screw Kit</a> should provide all the T Nuts =
and
screws for 4 camera mounts.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Other hardware required:<span style=3D'mso-tab-count:1=
'> </span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>M3x12 counter sink screws and nuts<br>
M3x16 counter sink screws</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in'>Something like <a
href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/binifiMux-360pcs-Countersunk-Phillips-Machin=
e/dp/B08N5XDHMW/ref=3Dsr_1_19?crid=3D196P290IBFZDR&amp;dib=3DeyJ2IjoiMSJ9.g=
vzEjpHlUXtRUJxoEfy2LEpecrorXRa4U0AvonuZ68bGjHj071QN20LucGBJIEps.9mlZXTiWlhK=
Vkd_YZJyZ39y5lbTpo9xxlc2fpYTdqK8&amp;dib_tag=3Dse&amp;keywords=3Dm3+m4+coun=
tersunk+screws+black&amp;qid=3D1747083121&amp;sprefix=3Dm3+m4+countersunk+s=
crews+black%2Caps%2C103&amp;sr=3D8-19&amp;xpid=3DuafD1Rm0VqlS3"><span
class=3DSpellE>binifiMux</span> M3 Screws Kit, 360pcs&nbsp;</a> will do 3 m=
ounts
and multiple Quad Cameras<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>M4x20 socket cap screws and nuts</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in'>Something like <a
href=3D"https://www.amazon.com/Kindroufly-Pieces-Button-Washers-Assortment/=
dp/B0BLCFZ2KL/ref=3Dsr_1_8?crid=3D3M30G8GZV1OEE&amp;dib=3DeyJ2IjoiMSJ9.b0HH=
Z39JgsBpPYjmkLwl92Ivk26csVFY0yC5r_z9v5oVA62XsyY91GPJ-KK7uyIUujUV6q1FLBVjKb9=
4RvyiIpXlmzHRI8gDvjJx5gsmsDE2z4Uty4XrHg_-wP9xyZkDo0JytrLxNgiGr8ROZ_Kj-BkNtN=
4tUjzkxPBpp_ViEa-1XF5vDv2mEG1eVDyWoRpbJLVUXFtOO378lAQgps2cmrxMmpNhBwBK-Xfd0=
3TIeSA._ytW4avdIe9tStc7Hfv0c5EEFIKOrgDsycMK60EF1xs&amp;dib_tag=3Dse&amp;key=
words=3Dm4%2Bcap%2Bbutton%2Bhead%2Bblack&amp;qid=3D1747083315&amp;sprefix=
=3Dm4%2Bcap%2Bbutton%2Bhead%2Bblack%2Caps%2C63&amp;sr=3D8-8&amp;th=3D1">382
Pieces Black M4 x 5/6 /8/10 /12/16 /20mm Button Head Socket Cap Screws</a><=
/p>
